history.content: Did you select 'waitlist if class is full' option when adding the class to your shopping cart? If there are no reserved seats available for your student status it will deny the enroll request (the class is 'full' to you), but you can enroll in the waitlist.

children.subject: You should email eecs-advising@eecs.berkeley.edu and let them know. Same thing happened to me. They told me that I have priority as a transfer, and then I went from waitlisted to enrolled that same day. Just make sure that you are on the waitlist, though.

history.content:
It seems I am unable to enroll into EE16a and the following error appears: "You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request. Note that waitlisted units will count toward the total units limit during each enrollment phase. Waitlisted units do not count toward financial aid eligibility."

For context, I am an new transfer in L&S.
history.subject: Unable to enroll into EE16A
